ad_v1_42final.label: ad_v1_42final.zip - Arcane Dimensions

ad_v1_42final.description:
This is version 1.42 - the newer, more feature-rich version 1.5 is available here.

Large-scale single player campaign with many new levels, some of them labeled as "test" maps, featuring a whole line-up of new monsters and items as well as several tweaks and changes to the gameplay. It is also meant to serve as a tool box for level designers. Map and QC sources are included.

Note: These maps require an engine port with increased limits, support for BSP2 and transparent textures. They are designed to be played with QuakeSpasm 0.91.0 or later.

A patch is available here.

This is version 1.5 which features even more new levels, enemies, items, and level functions. A patch for 1.5 is available here.

Note: These maps require an engine port with increased limits as well as support for BSP2 and transparent textures. They are mainly designed to be played with QuakeSpasm 0.92.0 or later.

ad_v1_70final.label: ad_v1_70final.zip - Arcane Dimensions

Large-scale single player campaign with many new levels, some of them labeled as "test" maps, featuring a whole line-up of new monsters and items as well as several tweaks and changes to the gameplay. Furthermore, it is meant to serve as a tool box for level designers, offering a large number of modified and new things to use in custom-made maps. Map and QC sources are included.

This is version 1.7 which includes various bug-fixes, additional features, and two new maps in addtition to ad_sepulcher.

Note: These maps (and likely all subsequent maps based on AD) require a source port with increased limits as well as support for BSP2 and transparent textures. Quakespasm 0.93+ is strongly recommended.

alk05.label: alk05.zip - The Savage Sanguine
alk05.title: The Savage Sanguine
alk05.description: Fourth in the Mel Soaring series, this map has you invading the mid-size base known as Sanguine. The level design looks great, a rusty old Strogg base, but is a bit confusing for having extra doors that lead to rooms you've already been in. The gameplay is solid as most other user-created maps. You start with both shotguns and a nailgun. There is a new enemy, Snakeman, who attacks you with two uzis which make a slightly faster nailgun. The final area may be a little tough for making you fight four Snakemen then two Shamblers in an area with only a pillar for cover. The pillar doesn't even help you since the Shamblers come from both sides of the room...
alk05.author: Shaun [Kona] Ross

alk07.label: alk07.zip - Egyptian Myth
alk07.title: Egyptian Myth
alk07.description: An excellent large Egyptian temple themed map that will keep you in the action almost the whole time. The level's new textures and geometry compliment each other quite nicely. The gameplay is very tight and recomended for intermediate Quake players. Every room has at least two enemies and often times after defeating them, a new set of enemies will spawn in the same room and assault you much by suprise. Most of the level contains Hell Knights followed by Knights, a few Shamblers & Vores, and the new Snakeman, who attacks you with two uzis (much like a nailgun). There is even a High Hell Knight for a boss, but he is mostly as tough as a Vore.
alk07.author: Shaun [Kona] Ross

alk08.label: alk08.zip - Charmhood
alk08.title: Charmhood
alk08.description: Small deathmatch level with a unique style and wave-based arena combat in SP mode. A DM-only version is included as well.
alk08.author: Shaun [Kona] Ross

alk10.label: alk10.zip - Permutations of the Rotten
alk10.title: Permutations of the Rotten
alk10.description:
"A new Nehahra episode by a non-Nehahra member, with a new story and setting. I believe the original idea of Quake was to be a dark world of rotting metal, wood and brick medieval, full of horrible monsters. The addition of base maps didn't help this theme at all. This is the way I imagined Nehahra to be, medieval fortresses combined with wastelands and industrial regions. So, inspired by Zerstorer, I set out to create a mini-episode that is dark and scary. Industrial mixed with medieval and metal, using ID's textures."

Four about medium sized tough maps in a strange and unique Metal-ish theme. Nice.
alk10.author: Shaun [Kona] Ross

alk11.label: alk11.zip - Grisly Manifest
alk11.title: Grisly Manifest
alk11.description: Large interconnected blue/brown Wizard map with several new monsters such as deadlier Ogres, axe knights, improved Hell Knights and the Scourge from SOA; a few new textures and quite tough gameplay. Nice.
alk11.author: Shaun [Kona] Ross

alk12.label: alk12.zip - Fearcraft
alk12.title: Fearcraft
alk12.description: "Three small-medium sized levels that are almost a horror Hexen2 theme. The setting is a dark fantasy castle showing hints of industrial growth, built upon terrain and cliffs, and disappearing into the void. The last in the 'Alk' series, it wouldn't be an Alk map without the onslaught of custom monsters. Fearcraft includes the SOA enemies, Baron, Axeman and some tougher Quake monsters. Not high in difficulty, Fearcraft will provide some enjoyable gameplay." Nice.
alk12.author: Shaun [Kona] Ross

alk13.label: alk13.zip - The Looming Madness
alk13.title: The Looming Madness
alk13.description: Large egyptian map with a unique mix of textures. Features a few custom monsters such as the SOA goblin and the Snakeman.
alk13.author: Shaun [Kona] Ross

alk15.label: alk15.zip - Brumal Quest
alk15.title: Brumal Quest
alk15.description: Large snowy medieval village, using Daikatana and Hexen2 textures, and coming with snow-themed monster skins.
alk15.author: Shaun [Kona] Ross

alkado.label: alkado.zip - The Alkado Adventure
alkado.title: The Alkado Adventure
alkado.description: Episode with seven small levels varying in theme, including start and boss map. Most monsters and items have new, strange-looking skins and sounds, some custom weapon models (e.g. from zer), and a bunch of new textures.
alkado.author: Alkado

alpha001.label: alpha001.zip - The Alpha Project
alpha001.title: The Alpha Project
alpha001.description:
Small Base map. Around id quality (=many unaligned textures).
This file was repackaged by Spirit. You can find the original .zip in the trash
alpha001.author: Jeff Popplewell

alsc.label: alsc.zip - ALSC Deathtrap
alsc.title: ALSC Deathtrap

altus2.label: altus2.zip - Altus Mors
altus2.title: Altus Mors

amphitoa.label: amphitoa.zip - Amphitheater Of Abaddon

anaconda.label: anaconda.zip - Anaconda

ananke.label: ananke.zip - Ananke 17

anevilnew.label: anevilnew.zip - An Old, Old Evil
anevilnew.title: An Old, Old Evil
anevilnew.description:
"This is the remnants of a project Tronyn and Murderous Martin worked on in 1997. It contains modified weapons and monsters mainly, as well as some experimental effects."

Barely an alpha version, slightly fixed up by aguirRe in 2006 - only listed here for archival purposes. The maps are unfinished and barely playable, either because they are bugged, lack monsters/gameplay, or are excessively hard. Furthermore, the cheat codes are disabled.

A few of the maps/areas eventually appeared in other projects by Tronyn, namely Soul of Evil and The Masque of Red Death. See anevil_readme.txt for more information.

anonca1.label: anonca1.zip - Anonca base: The shamblin
anonca1.title: Anonca base: The shamblin

anonca3.label: anonca3.zip - Anonca base 3
anonca3.title: Anonca base 3
anonca3.description: Medium sized blue metal base map with a unique theme.

anoxia.label: anoxia.zip - ANOXIA
anoxia.title: ANOXIA

ant.label: ant.zip - Antediluvian

aow.label: aow.zip - Around the World!

apdm3.label: apdm3.zip - Dead Best Friend

apsp2.label: apsp2.zip - Plumbers Don't Wear Ties (But They Do Carry Shotguns)
apsp2.title: Plumbers Don't Wear Ties (But They Do Carry Shotguns)

apsp3.label: apsp3.zip - Subterranean Library

aqua.label: aqua.zip - The Ancient Aqueduct

araivo.label: araivo.zip - Apinaraivo / Monkey Rage

arcol.label: arcol.zip - Arcol

area51.2.label: area51.2.zip - Area 51

The episode also features background music inspired by The Doors (can be turned off with "impulse 17") and a hidden fifth difficulty mode. The gameplay is fast and very hard, blending in with the strong 'Doom vibe' it conveys - especially the boss battle is extremely tough.

asl_1.label: asl_1.zip - Io. Lava Cleaning Base

bindingtower2.label: bindingtower2.zip - Binding Tower

Large map with a castle in a dark forest. Comes with a custom skybox and the map source is included.

The Borg cube from the Star Trek series, with new monster skins and sounds. Unfortunately, the map is utter crap - ugly, confusing, buggy.

copper.label: copper.zip - Copper Quake
copper.title: Copper Quake
copper.description:
A "Vanilla+" gameplay mod that introduces subtle tweaks to some of the game's core mechanics in order to make for a smoother experience. It is compatible with the original maps and most standard (id1-based) custom levels.

Summary:
  • Weapons fire is not blocked by monsters in death animations
  • Ring of Shadows makes enemies less accurate in combat
  • Vore missiles have a less-than-perfect turn rate
  • Ogres are 'partially' Z-aware
  • Zombie edge cases are fixed
  • Armor protection is proportional to current quantity
  • Nightmare skill is 50 max HP instead of turret-monsters
The mod is accompanied by a seperate custom episode: Underdark Overbright

Note: An updated version (1.11) is available here.
copper.author: Lunaran

"A totally total total conversion - pure fantasy style. A lot of maps with a great sense of exploration and discovery. This TC has new everything, and most of it is very good, though occasionally the new stuff can look a bit shoddy. There are some very cool details, and everything has a sense of fitting in well with the TC as a whole. Gameplay and maps are very different from Quake (which can take some getting used to), and usually very good - this is a most worthwhile TC."
- TEAMShambler

Note: A patch is available here

func_mapjam2.title: Func Map Jam 2 - IKblue/IKwhite Theme
func_mapjam2.description:
Map jam #2 - a community project at Func_Msgboard. The pack features 8 medium to large ikblue / ikwhite-themed maps. It comes with a couple of modified models and custom skyboxes. The map sources are included.

Note: Some of the maps require an engine port with increased limits.
func_mapjam2.author: Cocerello, ericw / FifthElephant, Lunaran, mfx, Scampie, skacky, sock, Tronyn

func_mapjam3.label: func_mapjam3.zip - Func Map Jam 3 - Zerstörer theme
func_mapjam3.title: Func Map Jam 3 - Zerstörer theme
func_mapjam3.description:
Map jam #3 - a community project at Func_Msgboard. The pack features 6 small to large Zerstörer-themed maps. The complete Zer mod is included in this release, and so are the map sources.

Note: Some of these maps require an engine port with increased limits and support for fog.
A hotfix for mfx's map is available here.
func_mapjam3.author: DaZ, ericw, ionous, mfx, Tronyn, scar3crow

func_mapjam4.label: func_mapjam4.zip - Func Map Jam 4 - Low Gravity Runic Theme
func_mapjam4.title: Func Map Jam 4 - Low Gravity Runic Theme
func_mapjam4.description: Map jam #4 - a community project at Func_Msgboard. The pack features 2 low gravity runic maps. The map sources are included.
func_mapjam4.author: FifthElephant, Rapowke

func_mapjam5.label: func_mapjam5.zip - Func Map Jam 5 - The Qonquer Map Jam
func_mapjam5.title: Func Map Jam 5 - The Qonquer Map Jam
func_mapjam5.description:
Map jam #5 - a community project at Func_Msgboard.

The pack features a start map and 8 maps of various themes made for WarrenM's Qonquer mod (included), which lets the player fight waves of monsters in arena-style maps, with the occasional assistance of minions. The theme for this jam was originally "Prisons of the underworld".

The map sources are included.

This file was repackaged by Spirit, the qcc/.DS_Store file was removed and the source/zerstörer.wad filename updated. You can find the original zip in the trash/ directory.
func_mapjam5.author: Arrrcee, FifthElephant, Hypnos, ijed, mfx, Scampie, Skacky, WarrenM

func_mapjam9_2.label: func_mapjam9_2.zip - Func Map Jam 9 - Contract Revoked / Knave theme
func_mapjam9_2.title: Func Map Jam 9 - Contract Revoked / Knave theme
func_mapjam9_2.description:
Func Map Jam #9 - a community project at Func_Msgboard. This pack features 15 Contract Revoked / Knave-themed levels of varying sizes. It comes with a start map and many custom models, sounds and skyboxes. The map sources are included.

Note: These maps require Quoth 2.2 and a source port with increased limits & BSP2 support as well as the -quoth command line switch.

This is an updated version of the pack which contains some bug fixes.
func_mapjam9_2.author: Bloughsburgh, Breezeep, DelusionalBear, dumptruck_ds, G1ftmacher,               Haunter, Ionous, Kell, Mukor, Naitelveni, NewHouse, onetruepurple, Pulsar, ShoTro, skacky

func_mapjamx.label: func_mapjamx.zip - Func Map Jam X - Insomnia Theme
func_mapjamx.title: Func Map Jam X - Insomnia Theme
func_mapjamx.description:

Note: These maps require a source port with increased limits and BSP2 support.
func_mapjamx.author: Artistical, Bloodshot, Fairweather, ionous, KalebClark, JCR, Mafon, Mazu, Naitelveni, NewHouse, Pinchy Skree, Strangework, Ukko, Yoder

Note: These maps require Arcane Dimensions 1.60 or later and a source port with increased limits.

This is the main office for Magnet Interactive Studios used as either a deathmatch or single player adventure level.

I ran vis about 30 hours on the bsp and it never returned, so it may be sluggish with the redraws and all. In this version, however, I did run vis -fast and it actually returned and doesn't display too many problems.
Ok, that was not that bad in 1996. ;)

Note: A late entry by Daya can be downloaded here.

The pack follows a Base theme and features five small to medium-sized levels, some of which add unique twists to the gameplay. A skill selection/start hub map is included.

Note: These maps require Quoth and an engine port with increased limits.
This file has been repacked for Quaddicted.
An updated version of NewHouse's map is available here.

middle.description: Large medieval town in a thundery night with completely new textures and non-standard gameplay. To proceed, it's often required to find hidden buttons and use certain strategies to defeat the monsters (such as relying on infighting and conserving ammo). Not for everyone.
middle.author: Jean-Marc Gruninger

mightarenas.label: mightarenas.zip - The Arenas of Might
mightarenas.title: The Arenas of Might
mightarenas.description: A simple arena with knights, not even an exit.
mightarenas.author: Justin, Kaepora Gaepora

mines.label: mines.zip - Mines & Mayhem
mines.title: Mines & Mayhem
mines.description: Small mine level with slightly confusing progression and some kind of future amazon enemy with a rocketlauncher.
mines.author: Ed Cope

mire_prison_jcr.label: mire_prison_jcr.zip - Mire Prison
mire_prison_jcr.title: Mire Prison
mire_prison_jcr.description: Small prison tract built into a dark mire cavern. The map source is included.
mire_prison_jcr.author: Jose C. Rodriguez (JCR)

misery.label: misery.zip - No campers palace, die with honor!
misery.title: No campers palace, die with honor!
misery.description: Smallish ugly mix-of-textures map. A demo and the map source are included.
misery.author: Marc Roussel

mission.label: mission.zip - MiSsIoN: ImPosSiBlE
mission.title: MiSsIoN: ImPosSiBlE
mission.description: Small mixed style map whose only highlight is an airstrike in the beginning (which is unfortunately downgraded by the lack of lighting on the jet). Barely average.
mission.author: Jamis Eichenauer

mjb_horse.label: mjb_horse.zip - A Horse Named Quake
mjb_horse.title: A Horse Named Quake
mjb_horse.description:
Small vertical medieval courtyard with a built-in skill selection room. The map source is included.

Note: This map requires Arcane Dimensions.
mjb_horse.author: Bloughsburgh

modjam_2019.label: modjam_2019.zip - Modding Jam 2019
modjam_2019.title: Modding Jam 2019
modjam_2019.description:
Modding jam event: eight small mods introducing new weapons, items, or gameplay features. Some of them come with test maps, new sounds and models etc. The mod sources are included.

[Cannot be run through the Quake Injector]
modjam_2019.author: aDaya, BloodShot, ish, JCR, khreathor, Redfield, Scrama, Shamblernaut

monastry.label: monastry.zip - Monastry
monastry.title: Monastry
monastry.description: Medium sized, fairly plain monastry with a semi-explorational gameplay and some new textures.
monastry.author: Neil Manke

monfree.label: monfree.zip - Project Monsterfree
monfree.title: Project Monsterfree
monfree.description: This is a singleplayer map with no monsters, just traps and obstacles - similar to the Hazard Course training map from Half-Life. Uses Rubicon textures.
monfree.author: PuLSaR

moonlite.label: moonlite.zip - Moonlight Assault
moonlite.title: Moonlight Assault
moonlite.description: Very large interconnected medieval castle with yards and outside areas - semi-nonlinear, explorational kind of gameplay.
moonlite.author: Tyrann

morbid_1.label: morbid_1.zip - Morbidity: 1
morbid_1.title: Morbidity: 1
morbid_1.description: Medium sized Base/Metal map. Uses some DOOM2 textures and some other custom ones. OK.
morbid_1.author: Daniel Vogt (MoRbId)

morbid_2.label: morbid_2.zip - Morbidity: 2
morbid_2.title: Morbidity: 2
morbid_2.description: Small to medium custom Metal map with a Base bit at the beginning.
morbid_2.author: Daniel Vogt (MoRbId)

mospq1.label: mospq1.zip - The Castle of Morpheus
mospq1.title: The Castle of Morpheus
mospq1.description: Large Wizard style castle with basic detailing and a dragon boss battle. OK.
mospq1.author: Tuomo "Morpheus" Tomperi

mountbase2.label: mountbase2.zip - Mountain Base 2
mountbase2.title: Mountain Base 2
mountbase2.description: This is the second version of Mountain Base, ostensibly being quite different in terms of gameplay.
mountbase2.author: Jarkko Heilio

movplan.label: movplan.zip - Shifting Planes Of Existence
movplan.title: Shifting Planes Of Existence
movplan.description:
Medium-sized Knave-style level with button-operated movable "planes".

Note: This map requires Quoth 2.2 and a source port with increased limits.
An updated version of the map is available here.
movplan.author: Spipper

movplan2.label: movplan2.zip - Shifting Planes of Existence (version 2)
movplan2.title: Shifting Planes of Existence (version 2)
movplan2.description:
Medium-sized Knave-style level with button-operated movable "planes". This is an updated version of the level. The map source is included.

Note: This map requires Quoth 2.2 and a source port with increased limits.
movplan2.author: Spipper

mrdrinc.label: mrdrinc.zip - Murder Inc.
mrdrinc.title: Murder Inc.
mrdrinc.description: Large interconnected base map with a unique theme and quite original gameplay. Uses a variety of new textures, e.g. IKBase. After arriving in a train, you have to infiltrate an enemy facility and work your way to the manager's office to blow it up.
mrdrinc.author: Isaac Barry (aka Clorox)

msacro.label: msacro.zip - Manslay's Acrobatics
msacro.title: Manslay's Acrobatics
msacro.description: Small Wizard style castle, made for SDA.
msacro.author: Dmitry 'Manslay' Dementjev

mstalk1c.label: mstalk1c.zip - Midnight Stalker
mstalk1c.title: Midnight Stalker
mstalk1c.description:
Medium-sized metal dungeon in E3M6 mashup style with a built-in skill selection room. It also features custom item boxes. The map source is included in the PAK.

Note: This map requires an engine port with increased limits. A standalone version optimized for vanilla Quake compatibility is available here.
mstalk1c.author: sock

mstalk1d.label: mstalk1d.zip - Midnight Stalker (v.2)
mstalk1d.title: Midnight Stalker (v.2)
mstalk1d.description:
Medium-sized metal dungeon in E3M6 mashup style with a built-in skill selection room. It also features custom item boxes. The map source is included.

Note: This is an optimized, stand-alone version of the level which stays within the vanilla Quake limits and does not require any special engine port. It does not include the custom item boxes from the previous version.
mstalk1d.author: sock

mungo.label: mungo.zip - Power Plant
mungo.title: Power Plant
mungo.description:
Medium sized fairly ugly Base map with a few rotating objects. Comes with a SP demo.

Note: This map has to be played with Scourge of Armagon.
mungo.author: Bryan L. aka Mungo

museum.label: museum.zip - Museum
museum.title: Museum
museum.description: Small museum with some custom textures and Quake art. Barely average.
museum.author: Steve Rescoe

mutant.label: mutant.zip - Mutant
mutant.title: Mutant
mutant.description: A small abstract mixed texture map which partly homages Doom II's map 1 ("Entryway").
mutant.author: digs

my_level.label: my_level.zip - Lost Underground Base
my_level.title: Lost Underground Base
my_level.description:
Third place in a competition of the Russian magazine Game.exe.
Medium to large base map with a warehouse, a mech hangar and a submarine port. A singleplayer demo is included.

Note: Originally named "my level.zip", renamed to "my_level.zip".
my_level.author: Denis Gusakov

mykd1.label: mykd1.zip - Mykd1
mykd1.title: Mykd1
mykd1.description: Medium sized Wizard/Metal map. CTF is supported as well.
mykd1.author: Mike Drummond

n3_100b2.label: n3_100b2.zip - oH gOd!
n3_100b2.title: oH gOd!
n3_100b2.description: necros' entry for the 100brush contest: a very small, ugly map using Quake2 and Zer textures.
n3_100b2.author: necros

n3sp02_13.label: n3sp02_13.zip - Castle Necrosis
n3sp02_13.title: Castle Necrosis
n3sp02_13.description: Large medieval castle with many custom textures, new features from Custents and a small boss map. There is also a bunch of extended files available to enhance the appearance.
n3sp02_13.author: necros

n3sp02_extd.label: n3sp02_extd.zip - Castle Necrosis (Extended Files)
n3sp02_extd.title: Castle Necrosis (Extended Files)
n3sp02_extd.description: Extended files for n3sp02_13: contains TGA texture replacements, skybox and music.
n3sp02_extd.author: necros

n3sp03.label: n3sp03.zip - At the Gates of Midian
n3sp03.title: At the Gates of Midian
n3sp03.description: Two maps: a large Metal/Wood fortress in the mountains and a small end battle arena,  featuring some modified Fiends and Shamblers. Conveys a certain DOOM-like atmosphere.
n3sp03.author: necros

nanesp1.label: nanesp1.zip - Catacombs of Misfortune
nanesp1.title: Catacombs of Misfortune
nanesp1.description:
Small dark linear catacombs.
This file was repackaged by Spirit. You can find the original .zip in the trash
nanesp1.author: nane

nastrond.label: nastrond.zip - Nastrond
nastrond.title: Nastrond
nastrond.description: Very large and detailed Knave fortress.
nastrond.author: Vondur

navybase.label: navybase.zip - The Navy Base
navybase.title: The Navy Base
navybase.description: Confusing and poorly built map. Starts on a ship ("navybase") and requires finding hidden buttons to proceed.
navybase.author: Gary Marshall (Zedek)

nazihell.label: nazihell.zip - Nazihell
nazihell.title: Nazihell
nazihell.description: Small Wizard house with talking furniture. Pointless.
nazihell.author: ET

ncroseum.label: ncroseum.zip - Necroseum
ncroseum.title: Necroseum
ncroseum.description: Small and very cramped orange/brown metal level.
ncroseum.author: Noel Weer

ne_deadcity.label: ne_deadcity.zip - The Rats in the Walls
ne_deadcity.title: The Rats in the Walls
ne_deadcity.description: Small oldschool brick level with a few DOOM textures.
ne_deadcity.author: necros

ne_dust2.label: ne_dust2.zip - CS INVASION FLEET!
ne_dust2.title: CS INVASION FLEET!
ne_dust2.description: Metal-style remake of the popular Counterstrike map de_dust2, created for a "Parody"-themed speedmapping session. Worth a laugh for those who know the original map. OK.
ne_dust2.author: necros

ne_lend_doom.label: ne_lend_doom.zip - The Living End & Elder World Waystation
ne_lend_doom.title: The Living End & Elder World Waystation
ne_lend_doom.description: A two-map SP unit: a large medieval dungeon in an underground lava cave (using rtGnosis textures), and a medium sized IKbase stargate facility. Great construction and detailing in both, though ne_lend might put some strain on slower computers. Also features a couple of new sounds and a skybox.
ne_lend_doom.author: necros

ne_marb.label: ne_marb.zip - Crescendo Of Dreams + Surmounting Terror
ne_marb.title: Crescendo Of Dreams + Surmounting Terror
ne_marb.description: Medium sized green DOOM marble/ wood level with a small end battle map.
ne_marb.author: necros

ne_ruins.label: ne_ruins.zip - The Altar of Storms
ne_ruins.title: The Altar of Storms
ne_ruins.description: Large ancient temple ruins hidden deep beneath a snowy mountain valley. The theme of the map is inspired by the Ayleid ruins from TES4: Oblivion. The map has all new textures, many modified or new monsters from Hexen 2 including a fearsome boss demon, and a custom quad-barrel shotgun.
ne_ruins.author: necros

ne_sp04.label: ne_sp04.zip - The Emptiness Without
ne_sp04.title: The Emptiness Without
ne_sp04.description: Large unique Metal-style space map. Also appeared in one of the Coagula contests.
ne_sp04.author: necros

ne_sp06.label: ne_sp06.zip - Once Upon Atrocity
ne_sp06.title: Once Upon Atrocity
ne_sp06.description: Large, spacious Q3Gothic-style fortress in a blood canyon, featuring some modified monsters and an evil dragon boss.
ne_sp06.author: necros

ne_tower.label: ne_tower.zip - Moldy Tower
ne_tower.title: Moldy Tower
ne_tower.description:
A medium-sized vertical map. It starts with a moldy green area from which you ascend into a mechanical exploratory part. After surpassing this you are awarded a tense boss fight. Lots of novel atmospheric effects thanks to the use of Quoth.

Note: This map requires an engine port with inreased limits.
ne_tower.author: necros

necrobrood.label: necrobrood.zip - Necrobrood
necrobrood.title: Necrobrood
necrobrood.description: "Necrobrood is a three map pack with new monsters, textures and skins. The theme follows on from Permutations of the Rotten with a very dark and morbid metal style using grotty brownish modified ID textures. A traditional Quake style but with a unique hand. A number of much stronger opponents with upgrades and improved AI to the Grunts, Enforcers, Ogres, Hell Knights and Shambler."
necrobrood.author: Shaun [Kona] Ross

nehahra.label: nehahra.zip - Nehahra
nehahra.title: Nehahra
nehahra.description:
17 maps by famous mappers, cutscenes, new monsters, great features. Comes with a custom engine. Extraordinary.

Note: You can turn off the new AI (side-strafing monsters) with nomonsters "1"

Note: This package was compiled by Spirit in 2008 because of the "mess of files" one needed to install, read the included readme_spirit.txt for changes. Mindcrime said it looked right but please report in if you spot anything faulty in the packaging.
nehahra.author: Nehahra Team

nesp09.label: nesp09.zip - Dawn of Eternity
nesp09.title: Dawn of Eternity
nesp09.description:
Large Metal/gothic lava fortress with a bunch of modified and new monsters, as well as a medium sized, hard secret map. Very high monster count in both maps, compensated by slight changes to some weapons and ammo system.

Note: These maps have to be played in an engine with support for higher edict count (versions of Tyrquake are included).
nesp09.author: necros

nightjourney_v2.label: nightjourney_v2.zip - The Night Journey
nightjourney_v2.title: The Night Journey
nightjourney_v2.description:
This is an SP episode consisting of six medium to large egyptian/wizard style maps (and a start map) with reskinned monsters.
"[ It ] was originally created by Dustin 'Tronyn' Geeraert and Darren 'Daz' Weekes and released sometime in 2003. Unfortunately, it was unfinished and had e.g. a lot of entity and progression problems." Therefore aguirRe fixed the maps up and re-released this version. The final map nj4 is still missing.
Gameplay is pretty hard. This pack has to be played with Q1MP2: Dissolution of Eternity.
nightjourney_v2.author: Tronyn, Daz, aguirRe

nihilore.label: nihilore.zip - Nihilore: The Mechanical Empire
nihilore.title: Nihilore: The Mechanical Empire
nihilore.description: Nihilore is a dark industrial two-map nightmare using a strong mix of custom textures. This Mechanical Empire is brought to life with rusting metal beams and buttresses holding together a brown brick city. Your enemy empire is strictly human themed, with dogs backed with improved Enforcer AI and four kinds of Human Grunts - all with new skins.
nihilore.author: Shaun [Kona] Ross

nike.label: nike.zip - Nike
nike.title: Nike
nike.description: Five small to medium sized realism maps with new textures. The mission is to infiltrate a 1960's Nike radar and missile base at night in order to obtain classified information. Uses custents.
nike.author: Brenda Ellen Perdion

nitemare.label: nitemare.zip - Nitemare
nitemare.title: Nitemare
nitemare.description: Medium sized base with a rocket bay. Bland.
nitemare.author: ViolentJ (Jeff Farris)

noturn.label: noturn.zip - No Turning Back
noturn.title: No Turning Back
noturn.description: Small Base? map with custom textures.
noturn.author: Geoffrey Overdorff

nsoe.label: nsoe.zip - Soul of Evil: Indian Summer
nsoe.title: Soul of Evil: Indian Summer
nsoe.description:
Medieval/fantasy episode consisting of five medium to large maps - sequel to Soul of Evil. Also features new and modified monsters, weapons and items as well as a story in the vein of SOE unfolding throughout the maps, many custom textures, sounds and skyboxes. Gameplay is somewhat non-linear and very hard.
Enhanced skins are available: regular and DP version.

Note: These maps require an engine port with increased limits.
An updated version of the episode is available here.
nsoe.author: Dustin "Tronyn" Geeraert et al

nsoe2.label: nsoe2.zip - Soul of Evil: Indian Summer (update)
nsoe2.title: Soul of Evil: Indian Summer (update)
nsoe2.description:
Updated version of nsoe, comes with a new map.
Medieval/fantasy episode consisting of five medium to large maps - sequel to Soul of Evil. Also features new and modified monsters, weapons and items as well as a story in the vein of SOE unfolding throughout the maps, many custom textures, sounds and skyboxes. Gameplay is somewhat non-linear and very hard.
Enhanced skins are available: regular and DP version.

Note: These maps require an engine port with increased limits.
nsoe2.author: Dustin "Tronyn" Geeraert et al

nyarlathotep.label: nyarlathotep.zip - Nyarlathotep
nyarlathotep.title: Nyarlathotep
nyarlathotep.description:
Two medium-sized experimental vertical maps with a unique flesh-temple theme and very uncompromising low-gravity gameplay.

Note: These maps require Drake and an engine port with BSP2 support.
nyarlathotep.author: Dustin "Tronyn" Geeraert

obiwan2.label: obiwan2.zip - Office of the dead
obiwan2.title: Office of the dead
obiwan2.description: Medium sized Metal map in a canyon, with a Base bit at the beginning.
obiwan2.author: Obi-Wan

obiwan3.label: obiwan3.zip - Blood of the Martyrs
obiwan3.title: Blood of the Martyrs
obiwan3.description: Medium sized Base map with somewhat confusing 'find-the-button-then-the-bars'-type of gameplay.
obiwan3.author: Obi-Wan

oblivion.label: oblivion.zip - Castle of Oblivion
oblivion.title: Castle of Oblivion
oblivion.description: Large interconnected Metal castle with a sense of exploration.
oblivion.author: Rick Lipsey

oblivion_2.label: oblivion_2.zip - O B L I V I O N
oblivion_2.title: O B L I V I O N
oblivion_2.description: Small space map with several floating platforms. Originally supposed to be the secret level of Ion Storm's Anachronox, but scrapped in later stages of the development and released a couple of years later. OK.
oblivion_2.author: Rich Carlson

obnejn.label: obnejn.zip - Oblivion Newton John
obnejn.title: Oblivion Newton John
obnejn.description: Small Speedbaze-themed level. The map source is included.
obnejn.author: Ruin

odyssey1.label: odyssey1.zip - Odyssey One
odyssey1.title: Odyssey One
odyssey1.description:
Large Wizard map. Can only be played in an engine with increased limits due to an excessive amount of lightmaps.

Get the fixed version instead: odyssey1_v2
odyssey1.author: Whitewind

odyssey1_v2.label: odyssey1_v2.zip - Odyssey One
odyssey1_v2.title: Odyssey One
odyssey1_v2.description: Large Wizard map. Originally created in 1998, this version has been rebuilt by Bengt Jardrup (aguirRe) to make it playable in modern engines.
odyssey1_v2.author: Whitewind (+Bengt Jardrup)

office.label: office.zip - Corporate Takeover
office.title: Corporate Takeover
office.description: A tower with hordes of monsters on each floor, connected by an annoying lift. No details whatsoever, neither any point in playing it.
office.author: The Omnimancer

offspring.label: offspring.zip - Offspring
offspring.title: Offspring
offspring.description:
Small ugly level with custom textures and uninspired gameplay.

Note: This map has to be played with Scourge of Armagon.
offspring.author: Chris Williams

ogitrev.label: ogitrev.zip - ogitreV taruggiZ
ogitrev.title: ogitreV taruggiZ
ogitrev.description: An upside-down version of Quake's original E1M8, created for an SDA contest. The GPL map source is included.
ogitrev.author: Ankh & id Software

ohzarm.label: ohzarm.zip - Ohzarm
ohzarm.title: Ohzarm
ohzarm.description: Medium sized base map with a few new textures.
ohzarm.author: Tony Boyer

old_city.label: old_city.zip - The Old City
old_city.title: The Old City
old_city.description: Small to medium-sized subterranean 'city' with Medieval textures.
old_city.author: Michael Cullum

oldhouse.label: oldhouse.zip - The Old House - the beginning
oldhouse.title: The Old House - the beginning
oldhouse.description: Very small, dark Wizard house. The start level of the then supposed to be forthcoming episode Paralyzed.
oldhouse.author: Mika Piirainen & Jouko Maksimainen

oldones.label: oldones.zip - Old ones
oldones.title: Old ones
oldones.description: Two very small Base maps which were already made in 2000 and also served as demo maps of some sort.
oldones.author: necros

omlabx.label: omlabx.zip - Laboratory X
omlabx.title: Laboratory X
omlabx.description:
A huge green base map with new textures and very hard gameplay (no difficulty settings, tight on ammo). The texture wad is included.

Note: This map requires and engine port with increased limits.
omlabx.author: ORL

oms2.label: oms2.zip - Orlmap Series 2: The first half
oms2.title: Orlmap Series 2: The first half
oms2.description: First half of a SP episode. Three medium sized canyon/ swamp/ Medieval temple maps and an unfinished Base map - many new (partly strange) textures. OK.
oms2.author: ORL

oms2_2.label: oms2_2.zip - Conflagrant Rodent
oms2_2.title: Conflagrant Rodent
oms2_2.description:
Large Medieval/terracotta-themed temple ruin in a canyon. High monstercount, hard gameplay. The texture resource wad is included.

Note: This map requires an engine port with increased limits.
oms2_2.author: ORL

oms3.label: oms3.zip - Cataractnacon / Zeangala
oms3.title: Cataractnacon / Zeangala
oms3.description:
Two large abstract base levels, "a lengthy journey through a non-linear H.R. Giger-themed flooded scrapyard". The map sources are included.

Note: These maps require an engine port with increased limits and expanded map boundaries. Currently, only RMQ (included) and Quakespasm (version 0.92.0 or later; set "sv_protocol" to "999") are capable of running them.

The maps can only be played on either Easy or Hard skill setting.
oms3.author: ORL

oms_unmentionables.label: oms_unmentionables.zip - Laboratory X & Neighboring Alcazar's
oms_unmentionables.title: Laboratory X & Neighboring Alcazar's
oms_unmentionables.description: Two old maps released for archival purposes: Laboratory X (oms24), a huge underground base with strange comic-style custom textures, and Neighboring Alcazar's (oms25), a medium-sized orange medieval fortress inside a canyon, which follows the same theme as Conflagrant Rodent.
oms_unmentionables.author: ORL

onepair.label: onepair.zip - OnePair
onepair.title: OnePair
onepair.description:
Pretty big weird-castle-like map in wizardish textures.
This file was repackaged by Spirit. You can find the original .zip in the trash
onepair.author: MadFox

opcondor.label: opcondor.zip - Operation Condor
opcondor.title: Operation Condor
opcondor.description: Very nice wizmetal map, the only drawback is that it gets quite confusing, each corridor looks the same. It's got nice traps and well made progression.
opcondor.author: Scott McNutt

orbit.label: orbit.zip - Orb's Betrayal
orbit.title: Orb's Betrayal
orbit.description:
Conversion of Quake II's map01, complete with textures and coloured lighting, but different monster placement.
This file was repackaged by Spirit. You can find the original .zip in the trash
orbit.author: MadFox

orion.label: orion.zip - Orion
orion.title: Orion
orion.description: Medium sized red brick/medieval map. OK
orion.author: Jason Fink

orlmaps.label: orlmaps.zip - Orlmap episode
orlmaps.title: Orlmap episode
orlmaps.description: SP episode with 8 medium sized Medieval/ Metal maps with some Base bits and a few custom textures (including start and secret level). OK, despite 'oldschool' construction with awkward brushwork in places.
orlmaps.author: ORL

ou.label: ou.zip - Witch House Mixtape
ou.title: Witch House Mixtape
ou.description:
Small to medium-sized wiztech level, industrial structures and crumbling brick buildings blending together.

Note: This map requires a source port with BSP2 support.
ou.author: czg

oum.label: oum.zip - Operation: Urth Majik
oum.title: Operation: Urth Majik
oum.description: SP episode with five medium to large IKBase/Quake2/Egyptian-themed, professionally constructed maps, some new monsters/weapons and progs including cutscenes - by FatController, Tyrann, Tronyn, and Apollo.
oum.author: Apollo, FatController, Tronyn, Tyrann

out1.label: out1.zip - Out of time
out1.title: Out of time
out1.description: Medium sized map, a short Base leading to Wizard areas with an underwater part in-between. OK.
out1.author: J.F.Gustafsson

out232.label: out232.zip - Mountain Base
out232.title: Mountain Base
out232.description: Small to medium-sized base map set in a canyon with two water treatment plants.
out232.author: NCMark

overflow.label: overflow.zip - Packet Overflow
overflow.title: Packet Overflow
overflow.description: Totally stupid and pointless arena combat map.
overflow.author: LZM

ovrridn.label: ovrridn.zip - Over Ridden
ovrridn.title: Over Ridden
ovrridn.description: Two spacious, medium sized base maps with a somewhat unusual theme and modified Grunts and Enforcers carrying SSG, NG, SNG, GL and RL.
ovrridn.author: Travis Almand

pabc3.label: pabc3.zip - The Courtyard
pabc3.title: The Courtyard
pabc3.description: Small brick castle with a courtyard. Barely average.
pabc3.author: Unknown

pabc5.label: pabc5.zip - Fortress Filbert
pabc5.title: Fortress Filbert
pabc5.description: Medium sized greyish fortress with some water bits. Barely average.
pabc5.author: Unknown

pabc6.label: pabc6.zip - Deathtrap Dungeon
pabc6.title: Deathtrap Dungeon
pabc6.description: Medium sized greyish dungeon. Barely average.
pabc6.author: Unknown

pabc8.label: pabc8.zip - Portal Endurance
pabc8.title: Portal Endurance
pabc8.description: Small blue brick map with a lava pool in the center. Barely average.
pabc8.author: Unknown

pagan.label: pagan.zip - Pagan
pagan.title: Pagan
pagan.description: Smallish and very basic Wizard/Medieval map.
pagan.author: Fredrik Martinsson

pagan3.label: pagan3.zip - The Pagan Temple
pagan3.title: The Pagan Temple
pagan3.description: Very small Metal map. Hardly more than two rooms. Pointless.
pagan3.author: Mike Melzer

pajitnov.label: pajitnov.zip - Pajitnov
pajitnov.title: Pajitnov
pajitnov.description: A small joke map inspired by Tetris.
pajitnov.author: R.P.G.

quoth.label: quoth.zip - Quoth
quoth.title: Quoth
quoth.description:
Quoth is an expansion pack for Quake 1 single player.

It is not intended as a series of thematically connected maps with additional custom content, as other packs are. The intention is to provide quality custom content for Q1 mappers and players in a single pak file. There are maps included in the pak, but there are also larger maps using the content already released separately by both Kell and necros, and more maps will surely follow.

Its features include technical additions for mappers, new monsters, and a couple of new weapons/items (additional information).

Currently you can play the first two maps of Quake rebuilt and remixed with Quoth monsters. The game will fail to load e1m3quoth because that map does not exist (yet). There are some test maps included for your enjoyment.

This is version 2.1 - a patch to version 2.2 is available here and version 2.2 (full) is available here.
quoth.author: Kell & necros

A rebalanced version of mfx's map from Retro Jam 1: a medieval building nestled in a rocky cavern and fronted by a lake of slime. Features traps and tough combat.

Note: This map is meant to be played with the retrojam1 pack.
retro_mfx_fix.author: mfx

retrojam1.label: retrojam1.zip - Retro Jam 1 - Medieval/Castle Theme
retrojam1.title: Retro Jam 1 - Medieval/Castle Theme
retrojam1.description:
Impromptu map jam following a "retro" medieval/castle theme: five small maps by ericw, mfx, Scampie, Skacky and sock. It comes with optional medieval-style item models, and the map sources are included.

Note: A rebalanced version of mfx's map is available here, and a fixed version of Skacky's map is available here. An expanded and polished standalone version of Sock's map is available here.
retrojam1.author: ericw, mfx, Scampie, Skacky, sock

retrojam1_skacky_b.label: retrojam1_skacky_b.zip - Dysnystaxis (...A Chance Meeting With Somnus)
retrojam1_skacky_b.title: Dysnystaxis (...A Chance Meeting With Somnus)
retrojam1_skacky_b.description:
A fixed version of Skacky's map from Retro Jam 1 (fixes an issue that made it impossible to load saved games): A small map set in a medieval courtyard and the surrounding buildings. Features somewhat non-linear gameplay.

Note: This map is meant to be played with the retrojam1 pack.
retrojam1_skacky_b.author: Skacky

retrojam2.label: retrojam2.zip - Retro Jam 2 - Fantasy Brick Cities in the Skies Theme
retrojam2.title: Retro Jam 2 - Fantasy Brick Cities in the Skies Theme
retrojam2.description: Speedy map jam following the theme "Fantasy brick cities in the skies": three floating maps by Skacky, Sock and RickyT23. It comes with optional medieval-style item models.
retrojam2.author: Skacky, sock, RickyT23

retrojam3.label: retrojam3.zip - Retro Jam 3 - Vertical Metal/Runic Theme
retrojam3.title: Retro Jam 3 - Vertical Metal/Runic Theme
retrojam3.description:
Third retro map jam: two "Vertical metal / runic"-themed maps by FifthElephant and skacky. The map sources are included in the pak.

Note: A "DLC" pack for Retro Jam 3 with three additional maps is available here.
retrojam3.author: FifthElephant, skacky

retrojam3dlc.label: retrojam3dlc.zip - Retro Jam 3 DLC
retrojam3dlc.title: Retro Jam 3 DLC
retrojam3dlc.description:
Three vertical metal/runic-themed maps - late entries to Retro Jam 3, ironically labeled "DLC". The map sources are included.

Note: ionous' map requires a source port with BSP2 support; skacky's map requires a port with increased limits.
retrojam3dlc.author: ionous, negke, skacky

retrojam4.label: retrojam4.zip - Retro Jam 4 - Episode 4 Tribute Theme
retrojam4.title: Retro Jam 4 - Episode 4 Tribute Theme
retrojam4.description: Four-day 'retro' map jam following an Episode 4 tribute theme. The result is eight small, dark and brutal levels by various authors. The map sources are included.
retrojam4.author: ericw, FifthElephant, ItEndsWithTens, PulSaR, TextFish, Scampie, Skacky, Zwiffle

retrojam4dlc_dw.label: retrojam4dlc_dw.zip - Ascension
retrojam4dlc_dw.title: Ascension
retrojam4dlc_dw.description: Small medieval/Episode 4-style level, originally started for Retro Jam 4. The map source is included.
retrojam4dlc_dw.author: DeeDoubleU

retrojam4dlc_pulsar.label: retrojam4dlc_pulsar.zip - The Elder Reality
retrojam4dlc_pulsar.title: The Elder Reality
retrojam4dlc_pulsar.description:
Medium-sized Elder World-style map that features at least one room from each level in the fourth episode of Quake (except for E4M1). An expanded version of the author's Retro Jam 4 entry.

Note: This map requires an engine port with increased limits.

This is the version with minor cosmetic fixes. Original file a27e2f42a2a42eb50eb99e6255db9494 is in the trash/ directory.
retrojam4dlc_pulsar.author: PuLSaR

retrojam5.label: retrojam5.zip - Retro Jam 5 - The Wind Tunnels theme
retrojam5.title: Retro Jam 5 - The Wind Tunnels theme
retrojam5.description: Fifth "retro" map jam held at Func_Msgboard, following a E3M5/The Wind Tunnels theme, resulting in seven small to medium-sized levels. The map sources are included.
retrojam5.author: Bloughsburgh, Breezeep, ItEndsWithTens, NewHouse, QMaster, Shamblernaut, skacky

retrojam6.label: retrojam6.zip - Retro Jam 6 - Egyptian theme
retrojam6.title: Retro Jam 6 - Egyptian theme
retrojam6.description: Sixth "retro" map jam - featuring 17 small to medium-sized Egyptian-themed levels by various authors. It comes with custom visuals for the items, several skyboxes, and the map sources are included.
retrojam6.author: Bloodshot, Bloughsburgh, Breezeep, Danzadan, DOOMer, dumptruck, FifthElephant, ionous, Khreathor, Lane Powell, MukOr, Naitelveni, NewHouse, onetruepurple, PuLSaR, skacky, Shadesmaster

retrojam6_negke.label: retrojam6_negke.zip - Egyptgington
retrojam6_negke.title: Egyptgington
retrojam6_negke.description:
Medium-sized Egyptian pyramid level, originally started for the Retro Map Jam 6 community event. The map source is included.

Note: This map requires either a source port with increased limits, or needs to be run as a mod using the included progs.dat file.
retrojam6_negke.author: negke

rettear.label: rettear.zip - Retinal Tear
rettear.title: Retinal Tear
rettear.description: A very well designed medieval map that could easily be one of the good old Quake maps by id. With better lighting and sexy brushwork this would have gotten the "Excellent" rating.
rettear.author: Taskmaster

rgdeep.label: rgdeep.zip - Deepest Oblivion
rgdeep.title: Deepest Oblivion
rgdeep.description: Dark oldschool dungeon level, originally made in 2019.
rgdeep.author: Daniel Remar

rgfire.label: rgfire.zip - Citadel of Fire
rgfire.title: Citadel of Fire
rgfire.description: Dark oldschool lava temple level, originally made in 2019.
rgfire.author: Daniel Remar

rhoqdoom_mbei.label: rhoqdoom_mbei.zip - Mars Base Excavation Incident
rhoqdoom_mbei.title: Mars Base Excavation Incident
rhoqdoom_mbei.description:
Large Doom-style level using original Doom textures. It starts out in a remake/conversion of E1M1 and provides a journey through various base and underground/marble temple areas, effectively using a Doom-like layout. Comes with a custom skybox and a music track.

Note: This map requires a source port with increased limits.
rhoqdoom_mbei.author: Rhoq

rhoqtdm2sp.label: rhoqtdm2sp.zip - Vivat Rex Lividum (single player version)
rhoqtdm2sp.title: Vivat Rex Lividum (single player version)
rhoqtdm2sp.description: Small to medium-sized blueish medieval level; the single player version of rhoqtdm2. The map source is included.
rhoqtdm2sp.author: Rhoq & negke

rin1m1.label: rin1m1.zip - Stalwart Stone
rin1m1.title: Stalwart Stone
rin1m1.description: Small Ebon-style level based on E4M4. The map source is included.
rin1m1.author: Qmaster

rings2.label: rings2.zip - Rings2
rings2.title: Rings2
rings2.description:
Very small arena combat map. Pointless.
Map source is included.
rings2.author: David White (NiX)

rit.label: rit.zip - Escape the Base
rit.title: Escape the Base
rit.description:
Small to medium Base map. OK.
This file was repackaged by Spirit. You can find the original .zip in the trash
rit.author: Chris Burgess

rit2.label: rit2.zip - Escape the Castle
rit2.title: Escape the Castle
rit2.description: Small to medium Metal map. OK.
rit2.author: Chris Burgess

ritualsp.label: ritualsp.zip - Dark Ritual (single player version)
ritualsp.title: Dark Ritual (single player version)
ritualsp.description: Medium-sized nightly industrial base where a dark ritual is being performed; the single player version of ritual, though slightly expanded. The GPL map source is included.
ritualsp.author: Tyrann & negke

rmx-pack.label: rmx-pack.zip - Remix Map Pack
rmx-pack.title: Remix Map Pack
rmx-pack.description:
Results of the 2008 remix competition at Func_Msgboard: five remixes/remakes of original id maps.

e2m1rmx by Spirit
e3m4rmx by Willem
e3m5rmx by Speedy
e4m1rmx by RickyT23
e4m7rmx by Zwiffle

Running the pack from a mod directory is optional - if one wishes to access the maps from the included start map.
(Some maps are released under the terms of GPL: sources)
rmx-pack.author: RickyT23, Speedy, Spirit, Willem, Zwiffle

rofra.label: rofra.zip - Reign of Ra
rofra.title: Reign of Ra
rofra.description: Very small level using sock's Egyptian textures.
rofra.author: super

roritor.label: roritor.zip - The Roritor Level
roritor.title: The Roritor Level
roritor.description: Medium sized Metal/Base laboratory with a few custom textures such as paintings and blackboards. Loosely based on the movie "Brain Candy".
roritor.author: Gregory Keen

rotcs.label: rotcs.zip - Retribution of the ConeScript
rotcs.title: Retribution of the ConeScript
rotcs.description:
A medieval/fantasy episode with 11 small levels. It is hub-based and features an RPG-like 'quest' gameplay. Comes with a complete set of replacement sounds and music.

Note: This episode requires Nehahra and it is recommended to use the Darkplaces engine.
rotcs.author: vIE888

royalwar.label: royalwar.zip - Royal Warriors
royalwar.title: Royal Warriors
royalwar.description: Small Wizard tower-like map. Nothing special.
royalwar.author: Scott McNutt

rpgsmse.label: rpgsmse.zip - Quake Condensed
rpgsmse.title: Quake Condensed
rpgsmse.description: Mini episode consisting of five small polished-up speedmaps, each following one of Quake's native texture themes.
rpgsmse.author: R.P.G.

rrp.label: rrp.zip - Rubicon Rumble Pack
rrp.title: Rubicon Rumble Pack
rrp.description:
Four very large industrial/base maps based on Rubicon 2. Includes a start map and introduces some new gameplay elements.

Note: These maps require an engine port with BSP2 support.
A patched version of the map telefragged is available here.
rrp.author: Hrimfaxi, ijed, mfx

rstart11.label: rstart11.zip - Reload
rstart11.title: Reload
rstart11.description: Short episode with five small Base maps. The mission is to infiltrate some bioforge facility, retrieve a genetic code stored on a keycard and return to entrance slipgate.
rstart11.author: Zied Rieke

rte.label: rte.zip - Return to Earth
rte.title: Return to Earth
rte.description: Four first maps with incredibly poor design, ridiculous textures, bad gameplay - apparently some sort of "joke" release. This file was repacked by Spirit.
rte.author: XeNoN

rubicon.label: rubicon.zip - Rubicon
rubicon.title: Rubicon
rubicon.description: Large rusty metal/industrial complex with custom textures, a few code tweaks, a start map and a cool Zelda tribute secret level.
rubicon.author: John "metlslime" Fitzgibbons

rubicon2.label: rubicon2.zip - Rubicon 2
rubicon2.title: Rubicon 2
rubicon2.description: Three-map base/industrial campaign with new textures, three new monsters, and a few other additions.
rubicon2.author: metlslime & czg

ruliano.label: ruliano.zip - Ruliano
ruliano.title: Ruliano
ruliano.description: Large stone map with many custom textures, several new monsters such as agents and cyborgs (?), a few new weapons, and some custom progs like rotation and cutscences. All text messages are in Spanish. OK.
ruliano.author: Rodrigo HernandeZ B.

rumours.label: rumours.zip - Recurrent Rumours
rumours.title: Recurrent Rumours
rumours.description: Large Wizard map with quite a bit of thematic varation.
rumours.author: distrans

runekeep.label: runekeep.zip - Rune Keep
runekeep.title: Rune Keep
runekeep.description: Non-transparent water version of runekeepgl: a large, detailed Medieval fortress.
runekeep.author: Rcktrob

runekeepgl.label: runekeepgl.zip - Rune Keep
runekeepgl.title: Rune Keep
runekeepgl.description: Transparent water version of runekeep: a large, detailed Medieval fortress.
runekeepgl.author: Rcktrob

runeofblood.label: runeofblood.zip - Rune of Blood
runeofblood.title: Rune of Blood
runeofblood.description:
Mini-episode consisting of three small levels and a start map. Some of the author's very first maps.

Note: These maps require Quoth.
runeofblood.author: Bloughsburgh

runerun.label: runerun.zip - THE RUNE-RUN
runerun.title: THE RUNE-RUN
runerun.description: Oh well, a sda (speedrunning) map. Ugly looks etc. If you desperately need something to play then go ahead, otherwise you won't miss anything by not playing this. ;)
runerun.author: Connor Fitzgerald

runfear.label: runfear.zip - Runic Fear
runfear.title: Runic Fear
runfear.description: Small to medium-sized runic level with an interconnected layout.
runfear.author: super

sadlark2.label: sadlark2.zip - The house of Sadlark (2)
sadlark2.title: The house of Sadlark (2)
sadlark2.description: Medium sized cramped odd Metal etc map.
sadlark2.author: Jonas N.P. Lindstrom

sadlark3.label: sadlark3.zip - The base of Sadlark
sadlark3.title: The base of Sadlark
sadlark3.description: Medium sized Base map with many oddly or unaligned textures.
sadlark3.author: Jonas N.P. Lindstrom

sadlark4.label: sadlark4.zip - The domain of Sadlark
sadlark4.title: The domain of Sadlark
sadlark4.description: Medium sized Wizard/Metal/Hiptemple map. Some buttons are hidden in secret areas.
sadlark4.author: Jonas N.P. Lindstrom

sadlark5.label: sadlark5.zip - The House Of Sadlark
sadlark5.title: The House Of Sadlark
sadlark5.description: A city courtyard / temple type map with heavy emphasis on RED textures, although e3 metal style is also present in some temple areas. Architecture and gameplay are vintage Sadlark-style: small and cramped with emphasis on small, efficient groups of enemy in extremely narrow confines. Enemy surprises abound everywhere. There are a few death-traps, but of the entertaining rather than frustrating variety.
sadlark5.author: Jonas N.P. Lindstrom

sadlark6.label: sadlark6.zip - The sacrifice of flesh
sadlark6.title: The sacrifice of flesh
sadlark6.description: Largish Metal map divided into four 'chapters'.
sadlark6.author: Jonas N.P. Lindstrom

sadlark7.label: sadlark7.zip - Dig me no grave
sadlark7.title: Dig me no grave
sadlark7.description: Medium "non linear (sort of) Sadlark metal style map."
sadlark7.author: Jonas N.P. Lindstrom

sadlark8.label: sadlark8.zip - Temple of Amon-Sadlark
sadlark8.title: Temple of Amon-Sadlark
sadlark8.description: Largish Egyptian-style temple with tombs, a few traps, and so on.
sadlark8.author: Jonas N.P. Lindstrom

sadlark9.label: sadlark9.zip - The four runes of Sadlark
sadlark9.title: The four runes of Sadlark
sadlark9.description: Smallish hub map, each branch in a different texture style. Nice.
sadlark9.author: Jonas N.P. Lindstrom

satanden.label: satanden.zip - Satanden
satanden.title: Satanden
satanden.description: Smallish bland Wizard/ Metal map with large rooms and very few monsters.
satanden.author: Unknown

satcath.label: satcath.zip - Satan's Cathedral
satcath.title: Satan's Cathedral
satcath.description: Medium-sized blue cathedral. Slighly buggy and may run slow on older machines.
satcath.author: Stijn Raiguel

sbe.label: sbe.zip - Scragbait's Estate
sbe.title: Scragbait's Estate
sbe.description: Large medieval brick estate with subterranean water caverns. It also includes a small start level and an unfinished end map.
sbe.author: Scragbait

sblue.label: sblue.zip - Sadistic Blue
sblue.title: Sadistic Blue
sblue.description: Small and cramped blue brick level in Azure Agony style with many Quad secrets.
sblue.author: YooShin Yang

sc_csmn.label: sc_csmn.zip - Can't Stop Me Now
sc_csmn.title: Can't Stop Me Now
sc_csmn.description:
Small oldschool base level.

Note: An updated version is available here.
sc_csmn.author: SgtCrispy

scampsp1.label: scampsp1.zip - Dead Memories
scampsp1.title: Dead Memories
scampsp1.description: Medium-sized idbase map with many crates and a critical slipgate malfunction.
scampsp1.author: Scampie

scar3sp01.label: scar3sp01.zip - The Ensnared Horizon
scar3sp01.title: The Ensnared Horizon
scar3sp01.description:
Medium-sized Ebon fortress/metal-themed level. The map source is included.

Note: This map requires a source port with increased limits.
scar3sp01.author: scar3crow

schist.label: schist.zip - Schist
schist.title: Schist
schist.description:
Episode consisting of 5 medium sized levels, a start and a secret map, some new textures and sounds, and custents stuff
The first few maps are bases in snowy canyons, the last few otherworldly castles.
schist.author: Noel Weer

scity509.label: scity509.zip - Quake City
scity509.title: Quake City
scity509.description: Medium-sized dark city/realism map with backyards, warehouses and sewers.
scity509.author: NCMark

scoop.label: scoop.zip - Scoop of chaos
scoop.title: Scoop of chaos
scoop.description: Small base map with an AAC in an outdoor area, a pumping station and a tank. OK.
scoop.author: J.F.Gustafsson

scorn.label: scorn.zip - Scorn Quake Level
scorn.title: Scorn Quake Level
scorn.description: An ok-ish blue metal map, quite confusing at moments but overall quite entertaining to play.
scorn.author: Michael Reed

scot2.label: scot2.zip - Ire and Abbeys
scot2.title: Ire and Abbeys
scot2.description: Very small ruined cathedral with a graveyard and arena combat. The map source is included. An early map by the author from 2009.
scot2.author: Qmaster

se.label: se.zip - Severe Exposure
se.title: Severe Exposure
se.description: Small to medium-sized base/industrial facility with a slightly nonlinear touch to gameplay.
se.author: Zied Rieke

seaview.label: seaview.zip - Seaview
seaview.title: Seaview
seaview.description: Small submarine base; features some material ripped from other mods, e.g. Scourge of Armagon and Zerstörer.
seaview.author: Daryl Deep

seraphim.label: seraphim.zip - The House of Seraphim
seraphim.title: The House of Seraphim
seraphim.description: Medium-sized puzzle map with Hipnotic/Metal textures. The layout is cramped and fairly nonlinear, the gameplay relies heavily on finding secret areas and hidden buttons.
seraphim.author: Peter van Wingerden

series1.label: series1.zip - Series 1
series1.title: Series 1
series1.description: Episode with six small to medium, poorly contructed and leaked maps in various texture themes.
series1.author: Inforatt (?)

sewage.label: sewage.zip - Sewage devastation
sewage.title: Sewage devastation
sewage.description: A big green swampy sewage system. Build in short time in a speedmapping fashion.
sewage.author: Hrimfaxi

sewer.label: sewer.zip - The Sewer
sewer.title: The Sewer
sewer.description: Small sewer map with a few custom textures and lava columns?!
sewer.author: Francis Fearon

sewer12.label: sewer12.zip - Seweage Playground
sewer12.title: Seweage Playground
sewer12.description:
Small to medium Base-themed sewer map with lots of pipes and an outside area.

Note: This map has to be played in Scourge of Armagon.
sewer12.author: Brian Kline (Larry)

sewerjam.label: sewerjam.zip - Quake Sewer Jam
sewerjam.title: Quake Sewer Jam
sewerjam.description:
Community mapping pack with 11 sewer-themed levels and a start map based on the Extras mod with a few additions, among which are two new enemies. It also features custom skyboxes and a few music tracks. The map sources are included.

Note: Some of these map require a source port with increased limits.
sewerjam.author: Andrew Yoder, Artistical, Axebeard, Burnham, Greenwood, khreathor, MortalMaxx, Nolcoz, Pinchy, Ryan Trawick, Ubiquitous

sfest97.label: sfest97.zip - Slaughterfest 97
sfest97.title: Slaughterfest 97
sfest97.description: Large 2D-ish map with an ugly hodgepodge of texture themes and architectural ideas. And a Baywatch poster...
sfest97.author: Brett Wilcock

sgc4.label: sgc4.zip - Notlob's Residence
sgc4.title: Notlob's Residence
sgc4.description: Medium sized, plain Wizard map. Somewhat of a sequel to sgc3.
sgc4.author: Steve Clarke

sgodrune.label: sgodrune.zip - Tale of Abbot's Rune
sgodrune.title: Tale of Abbot's Rune
sgodrune.description: Short story-driven SP "hub" with 3 maps. Very original style and gameplay!
sgodrune.author: Rain Rannu (Spacegod)

sgq.label: sgq.zip - Star Gate Quest
sgq.title: Star Gate Quest
sgq.description: Short base map, some good ideas but overall pretty bland. Comes with sounds from Half-Life which don't really fit (the weapon sounds at least). It also got a tiny skill selection map.
sgq.author: Ben Horsley

shadow.label: shadow.zip - Shadow over Innsmouth
shadow.title: Shadow over Innsmouth
shadow.description: Large medieval village with a few new textures and reskinned monsters. Somewhat of a sequel to "Village of Dread".
shadow.author: Steve Rescoe

shadowgl.label: shadowgl.zip - Shadow over Innsmouth (GL)
shadowgl.title: Shadow over Innsmouth (GL)
shadowgl.description: This is the GLquake version of shadow supporting transparent water.
shadowgl.author: Steve Rescoe

shaft29.label: shaft29.zip - Shaft of the Soulless
shaft29.title: Shaft of the Soulless
shaft29.description: One room with a "water elevator", struts and monsters. Very boring.
shaft29.author: Alan Troup

shafted.label: shafted.zip - Shafted
shafted.title: Shafted
shafted.description:
Small speedrunning map.
A nice challenge for speedrunners, but pointless for regular players.
shafted.author: David Hocking

sham.label: sham.zip - Sham
sham.title: Sham
sham.description: *Very* small (and very early?) wizard level. Map file is included.
sham.author: Chris

shamsp1.label: shamsp1.zip - Crown Of Thorns
shamsp1.title: Crown Of Thorns
shamsp1.description: Very small map with a blue castle in a canyon. Comes with a custom skybox.
shamsp1.author: Shambler

shamsp2.label: shamsp2.zip - Warmth Of A Dying Sun
shamsp2.title: Warmth Of A Dying Sun
shamsp2.description:
Medium-sized Egyptian-style level. Comes with a custom desert skybox.

Note: This map requires a source port with increased limits.
shamsp2.author: Shambler

shamsp3.label: shamsp3.zip - The Age Of The No Penis Mapper
shamsp3.title: The Age Of The No Penis Mapper
shamsp3.description:
Small joke map of sorts; a phallus worship shrine erected inside a slimey green cavity.

Note: This map requires a source port with increased limits.
shamsp3.author: Shambler

shesp1.label: shesp1.zip - Dorghael Arhlannen
shesp1.title: Dorghael Arhlannen
shesp1.description:
Medium-sized ikwhite-themed temple with nice gameplay and a boss-fight.

Note: This map requires Quoth.
shesp1.author: Sidhe

shkeep.label: shkeep.zip - Shadow Keep
shkeep.title: Shadow Keep
shkeep.description: Very small Wizard map with a water area.
shkeep.author: Glenn French

shoggoth.label: shoggoth.zip - Chapel Shoggoth
shoggoth.title: Chapel Shoggoth
shoggoth.description: Small to medium chapel with a graveyard and caverns beneath. Lots of back and forth running between the rooms.
shoggoth.author: Marc Laidlaw

shoot.label: shoot.zip - Shoot
shoot.title: Shoot
shoot.description: Very small and very pointless Medieval map (+ a skill selection map and three demos) unnecessarily bundled in a .pak. Source is included.
shoot.author: Étienne (Blood Man) Bégin

shoradar.label: shoradar.zip - Shoradar
shoradar.title: Shoradar
shoradar.description: Small level, a fort and a castle with abstract blue interiors in a canyon. Low ammo balance.
shoradar.author: Ben Watson

sickbase.label: sickbase.zip - Three Towers And A Sick Base
sickbase.title: Three Towers And A Sick Base
sickbase.description:
Large open base map set inside a lava canyon.

Note: This map requires Quoth and a source port with increased limits.
sickbase.author: RickyT23

siluette.label: siluette.zip - Silhouette of Darkness
siluette.title: Silhouette of Darkness
siluette.description: A medium sized medieval map with new textures, gameplay focuses largely on discovering secrets.
siluette.author: Neil Manke

simmer1.label: simmer1.zip - Security Base
simmer1.title: Security Base
simmer1.description: A small base map. The brushwork is promising but the gameplay is a bit boring.
simmer1.author: Qubix

simmer2.label: simmer2.zip - SIMMER2
simmer2.title: SIMMER2
simmer2.description: Nonstop Grunt Slaughter! The map is nice, some beautiful worked elements and good monster placement. You won't get a lazy moment. Also this map features a very good custom skin on the grunts.
simmer2.author: Qubix

simplex.label: simplex.zip - Simplex
simplex.title: Simplex
simplex.description: Large green jungle temple with some puzzles involving ancient machinery. Sort of a sequel to Ruins of Mazotac. The map source is included.
simplex.author: Andrew Yoder

sincinch.label: sincinch.zip - Sinister Cistern
sincinch.title: Sinister Cistern
sincinch.description: Around medium-sized blood cistern level using terracotta-style custom textures. The map source is included.
sincinch.author: Chris Holden

sisters.label: sisters.zip - Vampire Sisters
sisters.title: Vampire Sisters
sisters.description: Absolutely ugly and stupid medium sized map.
sisters.author: Bill Graham/billcat

skeet.label: skeet.zip - The Turkey Shoot
skeet.title: The Turkey Shoot
skeet.description: A shooting range with bouncing monsters. Fun for a couple of seconds.
skeet.author: Sid

sksp2b.label: sksp2b.zip - Conference of the Shamblers
sksp2b.title: Conference of the Shamblers
sksp2b.description:

sm24_than_se.label: sm24_than_se.zip - Title
sm24_than_se.title: Title
sm24_than_se.description: This map was originally made in two hours for the 24th Speedmap pack. For those who don't know, Speedmapping is simply to make a map in a set timelimit.The timelimit for this map was 100 minutes so I obviously failed :( Anyway, I made the architecture with 10 minutes left and added monsters in the following 15 minutes but was then blighted by compile problems and then stupid quake crashes. The first version of the map that was released (sm24_than) had no lighting, more bugs and worse gameplay. I quite liked the map so I decided to spend a little more time on itand re-release this special edition forQExpo.
sm24_than_se.author: than

smlevel.label: smlevel.zip - SM Levels Pack for QUAKE
smlevel.title: SM Levels Pack for QUAKE
smlevel.description: "The SM Levels Pack for Quake is a Partial Conversion utilizing some of the best QC mods that one can find. Some of the enhancements are the Chase Cam, Heads Up Display, a new Player Skin, a Flashlight, Flares, Ejecting Shotgun Shells, Gyro's Indecisive BOT for DeathMatch play, EarthQuakes, Rain, more Ambient Sounds, Exploding Walls, Gib Fountains and a few select NEW monsters. They are Willy the Spider, Snakeman (2 different types) and 2 surprise monsters. Most of Quake's original monsters have been modified in some way. I also added a few new weapons. The Pulse Rifle, Cluster Bombs and some Poison Gas Bombs are just waiting to be used on those who stand in your way. There are also a few other surprises." - 7 SP maps, including start and end map, 1 DM map

Note: These maps require a source port with BSP2 support as well as increased limits.
something_wicked.author: Tronyn, PM, Tyrann, necros

sop123.label: sop123.zip - The Source of Power

Mini SP campaign consisting of three medium sized outdoor levels (+ start map) in Wizard/ Canyon/ Egyptian style. Uses custents and has a few new monsters like improved Grunts/ Ogres and Mechs. OK.

Note: The maps are only playable in DOS/ Winquake or a high-limit engine. For regular GL engines, download the fixed version instead: sop_v2.
This file was repackaged by Spirit. You can find the original .zip in the trash

sop_v2.label: sop_v2.zip - The Source of Power

ter_shibboleth.label: ter_shibboleth.zip - Ter Shibboleth
ter_shibboleth.title: Ter Shibboleth
ter_shibboleth.description:
Episode with five huge, uniquely themed levels: a beach resort under a Golden Gate Bridge, a puzzle map set in an industrial storage facility, an Asian temple, a twisted otherworldly fortress, and a western mining town. Most of the maps use custom textures; the texture wads and the map sources are included.

Note: These maps require an source port with severely increased limits and BSP2 + protocol 999 support, such as Quakespasm 0.93.0 or higher.
ter_shibboleth.author: KenChennar alias Orl

ter_shibboleth_part_2_rev2.label: ter_shibboleth_part_2_rev2.zip - Ter Shibboleth Part 2
ter_shibboleth_part_2_rev2.title: Ter Shibboleth Part 2
ter_shibboleth_part_2_rev2.description:
The sequel to Ter Shibboleth, follwing the same boundary-pushing vein in three huge levels with impressive vistas: a snowy village in the mountains, the city of Paris (complete with Notre Dame and the Eiffel tower), and an ancient Roman city next to a colosseum. The levels run on the Drake mod which is included.

Note: These levels require a source port with increased limits and BSP2 support as well as server protocol 999. The memory heapsize must be set to at least 1 GB.
Due to the large open areas and no optimization (VIS), a considerable impact on performance should be expected.
ter_shibboleth_part_2_rev2.author: KenChennar alias Orl

terra.label: terra.zip - Terra
terra.title: Terra
terra.description:
Episode with 6 medium sized levels. Two Base maps, four mostly Wizard maps. Great design.
